    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Feature already in Vim?\r\n\r\nNo\r\n\r\n### Feature description\r\n\r\nNvim has `j` in `'formatoptions'` by default, but has the same default value for `'comments'` as Vim. This leads to surprising default behavior of `J` in files without a filetype, as mentioned in #6085, #8841, #8655, #11599, #16016, #19729, #20802, #25382. A less surprising default value for `'comments'` will avoid this, and many runtime `ftplugin`s already set `'comments'` to a different local value.",
